{"id": "38131", 
"title": "Bug 38131ajc needs -d option while correctly compiling classes from subpackage", 
"description": "Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println("Hello");
  }
}

Then compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

You will see a directory 'subpackage' created under the existing 'subpackage' directory. subpackage\Test.java
or
javac subpackage\Test.java

No big deal, really.", 
"OB": "When compiling a class in a subpackage using ajc command without the -d option, a 'subpackage' directory is created under the existing 'subpackage' directory.", 
"EB": "When compiling a class in a subpackage using ajc command without the -d option, a 'subpackage' directory should not be created under the existing 'subpackage' directory.", 
"SR": "To reproduce:
1. Create a class in a subpackage.
2. Use the ajc command without the -d option to compile the class.
3. Check if a 'subpackage' directory is created under the existing 'subpackage' directory."}
